{"title_page": "Ron Benner", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2020}}\n'''Ron Benner''' (born 1949) is an internationally recognized Canadian artist whose longstanding practice investigates the history and political economics of food cultures. He is also a gardener and writer who currently lives and works in London, Ontario.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://ccca.concordia.ca/bios/benner_bio.html|title=Ron Benner, Bio|website=ccca.concordia.ca|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>{{Infobox person\n| name               = Ron Benner\n| image              = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| other_names        = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = 1949\n| birth_place        = [[London]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]\n| nationality        = [[Canadian]]\n| education          = [[University of Guelph]]\n| occupation         = [[List of contemporary artists|Contemporary artist]]\n| years_active       = 1970-present\n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| partner            = [[Jamelie Hassan]]\n}}\n\n== Early life and career ==\nRon Benner studied agricultural engineering for one year at the University of Guelph (1969\u201370). Finding himself ethically opposed to bioengineering, he began to travel and research the politics of food, and work as an artist in London, Ontario.\n\nFrom 1971 to 1979, he worked as a brakeman and conductor on the Norfolk and Western (Wabash) Railway, and was a member of the United Transportation Union. In 1973 he began to travel frequently in Mexico, Central & South America, Europe, the Middle East and Asia. In March 1980, he attended the World Conference of Indigenous Peoples, in Ollantaytambo, Peru, as an official artist/observer.\n\nFrom 1975 through 1981, Ron was a member of the Forest City Artists' Association, and was manager of the [[Forest City Gallery]] in 1980\u201381. In 1983 he co-founded the Embassy Cultural House and served on the board until 1990. Co-organized the M\u00e9rida/London exchange (1980/81), as well as the Havana/London exchange (1988). In 1989 he was an artist/observer of the 3rd [[Havana Biennial]].\n\nIn 2000 he was awarded the Canada Council Studio in Paris.\n\nIn 2010 he was appointed Adjunct Research Professor in the Visual Arts Department, [[University of Western Ontario|Western University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vac.ca/ronbenner.html|title=Ron Benner - Trans/mission: Barley-Corn-Maize|website=Visual Arts Centre of Clarington|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nHis mixed media photographic installations are in the collections of the [[National Gallery of Canada]], the [[Art Gallery of Ontario]], [[Hart House (University of Toronto)|Hart House]] (The University of Toronto), [[Museum London]] (London, Ontario), McIntosh Gallery (The University of Western Ontario), The Canada Council Art Bank and the [[Casa de las Am\u00e9ricas|Casa de Las Americas]] (Havana, Cuba).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cacnart.com/ron-benner|title=Ron Benner|website=cacnart|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== Selected solo exhibitions ==\n\n* 2019 \u00a0''Trans/mission: Barley \u2013 Corn \u2013 Maize'', Visual Arts Centre of Clarington, Bowmanville, ON, a year-long site-specific installation responding to the architecture and history of the former barley mill, curator Sandy Saad<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vac.ca/ronbenner.html|title=Ron Benner - Trans/mission: Barley-Corn-Maize|website=Visual Arts Centre of Clarington|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2017-  ''Trans/mission: Native to the Americas,'' permanent photographic/garden installation, sunken garden of the Wilfrid Laurier Library, organized by the Robert Langen Art Gallery, Wilfrid Laurier University, Waterloo, ON<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://library.wlu.ca/events/exhibition-transend-meeting-room|title=Exhibition: Transend: Meeting Room|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* 2017 \u00a0''Transend: Meeting Room'', Robert Langen Art Gallery, [[Wilfrid Laurier University]], Waterloo, ON, curator Suzanne Luke<ref name=\":2\" />\n* 2016/17 ''Trans/mission: 101,'' photographic/garden installation, [https://kwag.ca/ Kitchener-Waterloo Art Gallery], Kitchener, ON, curator Crystal Mowry presented in concert with CAFKA 16 (Contemporary Art Forum Kitchener Area)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kwag.ca/content/ron-benner-transmission-101|title=Ron Benner // Trans/mission: 101|last=smitchell|date=2017-05-17|website=kwag.ca|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2015\u00a0''Ron Benner: 3 Questions'', McIntosh Gallery, Western University, London, ON, curator Julian Haladyn<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mcintoshgallery.ca/exhibitions/past/2015.html|title=2015|website=mcintoshgallery.ca|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2015  ''All That Has Value'', 3 guerrilla garden installations, in collaboration with CUPE, London, ON\n* 2015 \u00a0''In Digestion'', [[Museum London]], London, ON<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://museumlondon.ca/exhibitions/in-digestion|title=Exhibitions - Museum London|website=museumlondon.ca|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2013\u00a0 ''Insubstantial Equivalence'', photographic/garden installation, curator Peter Dykhuis, on the university campus in partnership with the agricultural faculty and the Dalhousie Art Gallery, Halifax, NS<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dal.ca/news/2013/10/03/food-for-thought.html|title=Food for thought|website=Dalhousie News|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2012-15 \u00a0''Cuitlacoche \u2013 Your\u00a0 Disease Our Delicacy'',\u00a0 photographic/garden installation, curator Su Ying\u00a0 Lee, Hart House and Justina M. Barnicke Gallery, University of Toronto, Toronto, ON<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artmuseum.utoronto.ca/exhibition/ron-benner-disease-delicacy-cuitlacoche/|title=Ron Benner: Your Disease Our Delicacy (cuitlacoche)|website=Art Museum at the University of Toronto|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2010 \u00a0''/10'', photographic/garden installation, curator Vicky Chainey Gagnon, site project on campus, [[Bishop's University]], Sherbrooke, Qu\u00e9bec<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.foreman.ubishops.ca/fileadmin/foreman_documents/images/exhibitions/2010-2011/ron_benner/Press_Release_Ron_Benner_FINAL.pdf|title=/10, A GARDEN PROJECT BY RON BENNER|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* 2008 \u00a0''Trans/mission: Bl\u00e9 d\u2019Inde'', photographic/garden installation, curator Hannah Claus, Axen\u00e907, Gatineau, Qu\u00e9bec<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Thomas, Jeff|last2=Gill, Rajdeep Singh|date=2008|title=Trans/mission : Bl\u00e9 d'Inde : Ron Benner|url=https://core.ac.uk/display/43531807|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n* 2005-  \u00a0 ''As the Crow Flies'', photographic/water garden installation, [[Museum London]], London, ON<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ccahtecrossingborders.blogspot.com/2008/07/as-crow-flies-ron-benners-garden.html|title=Arts Crossing Borders: As the Crow Flies Ron Benner's Garden Installation Raises Awareness About Unequal Distribution of Food|last=Mclean|first=Cheryl|date=2008-07-16|website=Arts Crossing Borders|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2005-09 ''Trans/mission: Still Life'', photographic/garden installations, co-ordinated through McIntosh Gallery, Western University, Grosvenor Lodge, London, ON\n* 2005 ''Trans/mission: Pineapple Vectors,'' [[Telegraph House]], Port Stanley, ON\n*2003 ''Re-viewed'', [[Art Gallery of Ontario]], Toronto, Ontario.\n* 2003 ''Trans/mission: Vectors'', Expression, [[Saint-Hyacinthe]], Qu\u00e9bec.\n* 2003-02 ''Trans/mission: African Vectors'', [http://www.oakvillegalleries.com Oakville Galleries], Oakville, Ontario.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.oakvillegalleries.com/tag/ron-benner/|title=Ron Benner {{!}} Oakville Galleries|last=Zanetti|first=Maria|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* 2002 ''Photographs 1997-2002'', Colour by Schubert, London, Ontario.\n* 1999 ''Capital Remains'', London Regional Art and Historical Museums, London, Ontario.\n* 1997/01 ''Trans/mission: Corn Vectors'', [[University of Western Ontario]], London, Ontario.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://plepuc.org/en/artwork/transmission-corn-vectors|title=Trans/mission: Corn Vectors|website=Pr\u00e9sences du litt\u00e9raire dans l\u2019espace public canadien|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* 1997/01  ''The Commodification of Life'', public project, Ontario New Democratic Party Convention, [[Hamilton Convention Centre]], Hamilton, Ontario.\n* 1997 ''In Digestion - Recent Acquisitions'', London Regional Art & Historical Museums, London, Ontario.\n* 1996/95 ''All That Has Value'', national touring exhibition: McIntosh Gallery, University of Western Ontario and Covent Garden Market, London, Ontario; Edmonton Art Gallery, Edmonton, Alberta; Presentation House Gallery, Vancouver, British Columbia; Dunlop Art Gallery, Regina, Saskatchewan. Curated by Peter White.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thepolygon.ca/exhibition/ron-benner-all-that-has-value/|title=Ron Benner: All That Has Value|date=2011-01-20|website=The Polygon|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mcintoshgallery.ca/about/history.html|title=History - McIntosh Gallery - Western University|website=mcintoshgallery.ca|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* 1995 ''ANTHRO-APOLOGIES, Peru 1979-80'', [[Art Gallery of Ontario]], Toronto, Ontario.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.virtualmuseum.ca/sgc-cms/histoires_de_chez_nous-community_stories/pm_v2.php?id=record_detail&fl=0&lg=English&ex=00000842&rd=253495|title=Representations: YYZ in the 80s|website=www.virtualmuseum.ca|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* 1992  ''\u00bfValia La Pena?/ Nat\u00edvas De Las Am\u00e9ricas'', Billboard Installation, La Carboneria Sevilla, Spain.\n* 1991  ''Selected Works 1976-90'', Galerie Brenda Wallace, Montr\u00e9al, Qu\u00e9bec.\n* 1989  ''Ron Benner: Other Lives'', [[Art Gallery of Windsor]], Windsor, Ontario. Curated by Matthew Teitelbaum.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://agw.ca/exhibition/43|title=Ron Benner: As dark as the grave wherein my friend is laid|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* 1988  ''Bahia de Cochinos/ Bay of Pigs'', [[Mercer Union]], Toronto, Ontario.\n* 1988  ''Ron Benner: Other Lives'', [[Mendel Art Gallery]], Saskatoon, Saskatchewan. Curated by Matthew Teitelbaum.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abebooks.com/book-search/title/ron-benner/|title=Ron Benner - AbeBooks|website=www.abebooks.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== Selected group exhibitions ==\n\n* 2020 ''Enawenndewin/Relationships'' curated by William Kingfisher, [[McMaster Museum of Art]], [[McMaster University]], Hamilton, ON \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0\n* 2019\u00a0''Enawendewin Project, ''Artspace Gallery,''\u00a0''Peterborough, Ontario, curated by William Kingfisher<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artspace-arc.org/exhibition/enawendewin-relationships/|title=enawendewin/relationships {{!}} Artspace|website=artspace-arc.org|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2019 ''The World is a Garden: Jamelie Hassan & Ron Benner'', SB Contemporary, Windsor, ON\n* 2019 ''401 West! Portrait of a Region'', Art Gallery of Windsor, Windsor, ON\n* 2018 ''Imago Mundi'', Onsite Gallery, Toronto, curator [https://www.linkedin.com/in/francesca-valente-4b810332/?originalSubdomain=ca Francesca Valente]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www2.ocadu.ca/event/imago-mundi-%E2%80%94-great-and-north|title=Imago Mundi \u2014 Great and North|last=134851139863553|last2=134851139863553|date=2018-08-16|website=OCAD UNIVERSITY|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2017 ''Imago Mundi'', Venice, Italy, curator [https://www.linkedin.com/in/francesca-valente-4b810332/?originalSubdomain=ca Francesca Valente]\n* 2016 ''Toronto: Tributes and Tributaries, 1971-1989'', Art Gallery of Ontario, Toronto, curator [[Wanda Nanibush]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ago.ca/publication/toronto-tributes-tributaries-1971-1989|title=Toronto: Tributes + Tributaries, 1971\u20131989|website=Art Gallery of Ontario|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2016 ''A Line Has Two Sides, Faculty and Staff Exhibition,'' Art Lab, Western University, London, ON, curator Susan Edelstein\n* 2015 ''The Second Silk Road International Festival'', Xi'an, China\n* 2015 ''The Transformation of Canadian Landscape Art: The Inside and Outside of Being,'' [[Today Art Museum]], Beijing, China<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.todayartmuseum.com/enexhdetails.aspx?id=543|title=TODAY ART MUSEUM {{!}} The Transformation of Canadian Landscape Art Inside&Outside of Being|website=www.todayartmuseum.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2014 ''The World is a Garden while the Walls are the State, Jamelie Hassan and Ron Benner,'' A Space Gallery, Toronto, curator Vicky Moufawad-Paul<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aspacegallery.org/index.php?m=programdetails&id=755|title=A Space Gallery|website=www.aspacegallery.org|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2014 ''The Transformation of Landscape Art in Canada: The Inside and Outside of Being,'' curators Zhou Yan and Yang Chao, off-site project, Great Tang All Day Mall, Xi'an Art Museum, Xi'an, China<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xianartmuseum.org/exhibit.asp?id=477|title=.:::\u897f\u5b89\u7f8e\u672f\u9986-\u666f\u89c2\u4e4b\u53d8\uff1a\u52a0\u62ff\u5927\u827a\u672f\u4e2d\u4eba\u4e0e\u98ce\u666f\u7684\u6539\u9020:::.|website=www.xianartmuseum.org|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2014 ''Futurity & Photography,'' Westland Art Gallery, London, ON, curator Troy Ouellette\n* 2014 ''Resistance,'' Manif d'art 7, Quebec City Biennial, off-site project in bus shelters in two locations in Quebec City, curator, Vicky Chainey Gagnon\n* 2013 ''Sample, Faculty and Staff Exhibition,'' curator Susan Edelstein, Art Lab, University of Western, London, ON\n* 2013 ''The World is a Garden'', 2 person exhibition with Jamelie Hassan, Biblioteca Andr\u00e9s Henestrosa, Oaxaca,\u00a0Mexico, curator Freddy Aguilar\n* 2012 ''Bread & Butter,'' Jackman Humanities Institute/Hart House, University of Toronto, ON, curator Sandy Saad in collaboration with Barbara Fischer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://artmuseum.utoronto.ca/exhibition/bread-and-butter/|title=Bread and Butter|website=Art Museum at the University of Toronto|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2012 ''Place Markers:Mapping Locations and Probing'' \u00a0group exhibition, [http://artgallery.dal.ca/ Dalhousie Art Gallery], Halifax, NS, curator Peter Dykhuis\n* 2011 Windsor Biennial, curator Ian Baxter, Art Gallery of Windsor, Windsor, ON\n* 2011 ''Where will you be in eternity?'' Thielsen Gallery, London, ON\n* 2010 ''Nuit Blanche Retrospective'', Bank of Nova Scotia Building, Toronto, ON\n* 2010 ''Growing Histories,'' [http://www.foreman.ubishops.ca/exhibitions.html Foreman Art Gallery], Bishop's University, Sherbrooke, Qu\u00e9bec, curator Genevieve Chevalier and Vicky Chainey Gagnon\n* 2010 ''Natural.Disaster'', McIntosh Gallery, University of Western Ontario, London, ON, curator Jessica Wyman\n* 2010 ''Minamata/Tunnel Vision'', recent acquisitions, [https://www.agw.ca/ The Art Gallery of Windsor], Windsor, ON\n* 2009 ''Home/land & Security'', Render Gallery, University of Waterloo, Waterloo, ON, curator Jeff Thomas\n* 2009 ''Orange:'' ''Aesthetics & Ethics'', Expression, Saint-Hyacinthe, Qu\u00e9bec, curator Marcel Blouin\n* 2006 \u2013 08 \u00a0 ''Orientalism & Ephemera'', curator Jamelie Hassan, Art Metropole, Toronto, Art Gallery of Windsor, Windsor; Ottawa Art Gallery, Ottawa; Centre A Gallery, Vancouver, BC.;\u00a0 Art Gallery of the University of Saskatchewan, Saskatoon, Sask.\n* 2007 ''Bordercases: The Wall'', The Art Gallery of Windsor, Windsor, ON\n* 2006 ''Science in Art,'' [[Universit\u00e9 du Qu\u00e9bec \u00e0 Montr\u00e9al|UQAM]], Montr\u00e9al, Qu\u00e9bec\n* 2006 ''La Nuit Blanche,'' artists project : ''corn roast/ maize barbacoa'', City of Toronto, curators Fern Bayer, Peggy Gale and Chrysanne Stathacos\n* 2006 ''Art Against War,'' Cube Gallery, Ottawa'','' Ont. Exhibiting artist and co-coordinator with Don Monet and Jamelie Hassan\n* 2006 ''Not Sheep : New Urban Enclosures and Commons'', Artspeak Gallery, Vancouver, BC<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://artspeak.ca/archive/|title=Archive {{!}} Artspeak|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2005 ''Beyond Bounds'': ''Art in London 1970 -1987'', curator Robert McKaskell, Museum London, London, ON\n* 2005 ''Homerun'', ''Recent Acquistions'', [[Museum London]], London, ON\n* 2005 ''Paradigms of Citizenship'', McIntosh Gallery, The University of Western Ontario, London, ON\n*2004 ''Open Air 2:'' ''Gateways & Gardens, (Trans/mission: Still Life)'', Grosvenor Lodge, University of Western Ontario, London, Ontario.\n*2004 ''Home & Away'', (Ron Benner, Jamelie Hassan, John Tamblyn & Larry Towell), Michael Gibson Gallery, London, ON<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gibsongallery.com/news/2016-year-review/|title=2016 Year in Review|website=Michael Gibson Gallery|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* 2003 ''Looking Left'', Articule, Montr\u00e9al, Qu\u00e9bec.\n* 2003 ''[http://www.expression.qc.ca/orange/ Orange (markets)]'', Expression, Saint-Hyacinthe, Qu\u00e9bec.\n* 2003 ''Bookworks on the Fence'', organized by [[Red Tree Collective]], Toronto, Ontario; Epicentro, Mexico City, Mexico and Museum of Vera Cruz, Mexico.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.redtreecollective.ca/home.htm|title=red tree home|website=www.redtreecollective.ca|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* 2002 ''To Eat or Not To Eat'', Art Centre of Salamanca, Salamanca, Spain.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.absolutearts.com/artsnews/2002/11/20/30501.html|title=To Eat or Not To Eat - Centro De Arte Salamanca - Absolutearts.com|website=www.absolutearts.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\